description:
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature eats too much code. When adding a parameter to the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method, the code assist should only replace the necessary portion of the code. However, it replaces more code than necessary.

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a class similar to the enclosed class:

public class X {
  void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo());
  }

  int foo() {
    return 5;
  }

  void baz(int i, int j) {
    // code implementation
  }
}

2. Invoke the code assist feature when adding a parameter to the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method.

Expected Behavior:
The code assist should only replace the portion of the code that needs to be modified, without replacing more code than necessary.

Observed Behavior:
The code assist replaces more code than necessary.

Additional Information:
- The text to replace is computed by the code assist infrastructure.
- An option to control the amount of source to replace was added and then removed later.
- The choice between replacing until the end or until the cursor location should be conditioned by a keystroke (e.g. enter = replace until end, insert = replace until cursor location).

Note: This bug report has been moved to ITPJUI.
